# This project

- **Stack:** [LiveKit Agents](https://github.com/livekit/agents) (Python) for voice AI; intended for **LiveKit Cloud**. Product and setup context: **`README.md`**.
- **Package manager:** Always **`uv`** — install, run the agent, run tests (`uv sync`, `uv run …`).
- **Layout:** Code under **`src/`**. Keep **`agent.py` as the entrypoint** (see Dockerfile). Extra modules are fine.
- **Format/lint:** `uv run ruff format` and `uv run ruff check`.

## Workflows (latency)

Prefer **handoffs** and **tasks** over one huge prompt for every phase. Minimize tools and context per LLM call. Docs: [workflows](https://docs.livekit.io/agents/build/workflows/).

## When to open `README.md`

Use **`README.md`** (not only rules) for: first-time setup; **`uv run python src/agent.py download-files`**; **`console` / `dev` / `start`**; evals; Docker/deploy; **`uv.lock`** / **`livekit.toml`**; linked web/mobile/telephony starters; **self-host vs Cloud** (plugins vs Inference).

## Where coding-agent guidance lives

Substance is in **`.cursor/rules/*.mdc`**. **`AGENTS.md`** is only a pointer for tools that require it.

**Glob-scoped rules:** `livekit-voice-agents.mdc` and `livekit-testing.mdc` attach when **`src/**/*.py`** or **`tests/**/*.py`** are in context. For design-only chats, include those paths (e.g. open a file) so those rules apply.

For LiveKit APIs, still use **`lk docs`**, **LiveKit docs MCP** (`livekit-docs`), or [docs.livekit.io](https://docs.livekit.io) — rules do not replace current API docs.
